NAME
    Dist::Zilla::Plugin::Authority - add an $AUTHORITY to your packages

DESCRIPTION
    This plugin adds the $AUTHORITY marker to your packages. Also, it can
    add the authority information to the metadata, if requested.

            # In your dist.ini:
            [Authority]
            authority = cpan:APOCAL
            do_metadata = 1

    This plugin accepts the following options:

    *   authority

        The authority you want to use. It should be something like
        "cpan:APOCAL". Required.

    *   do_metadata

        A boolean value to control if the authority should be added to the
        metadata. Defaults to false.

        The metadata will look like this:

                x_authority => 'cpan:APOCAL'

